# Walkthrough - Stage 1 Location Hunt Fix

I have fixed the issue where "Mohawk - Outside" was being incorrectly identified as a valid artist location. This was caused by Stage 1 of the location hunt pipeline checking the `venueName` field and the secondary validation being too permissive with hyphenated venue-style strings.

## Changes Made

### Core Logic

#### [location.ts](file:///c:/Users/kp/Documents/spectral-soundworks-app/src/lib/location.ts)
- **Removed `venueName`** from the Stage 1 `fromRawFields` check. Venues are almost never the artist's home location and were leading to "bunk" results.
- **Improved `validLocation` validation**:
    - Added **"mohawk"** to the location blacklist.
    - Added a **hyphenated string check**: Strings containing " - " are now rejected if they don't also contain a comma (which usually indicates a City, State or Venue, City, State format). This specifically catches "Venue - Stage" patterns like "Mohawk - Outside".

## Verification Results

### Automated Tests
I created a verification script [test-location-fix.js](file:///c:/Users/kp/Documents/spectral-soundworks-app/scratch/test-location-fix.js) which tests the logic against various samples:

| Input | Expected | Result |
|-------|----------|--------|
| "Austin, TX" | "Austin, TX" | ✅ Pass |
| "Brooklyn" | "Brooklyn" | ✅ Pass |
| "Mohawk - Outside" | `null` | ✅ Pass |
| "Mohawk" | `null` | ✅ Pass |
| "Stubb's - Indoor" | `null` | ✅ Pass |
| "Worldwide" | `null` | ✅ Pass |
| "Austin, TX - Mohawk" | "Austin, TX - Mohawk" | ✅ Pass |

> [!NOTE]
> Strings like "Austin, TX - Mohawk" are still allowed because they contain a comma, suggesting they contain at least some valid geographic data (Austin, TX), even if a venue name is attached. This preserves data quality for detailed location strings.

### Manual Verification
- Verified that `location.ts` is correctly updated and Stage 1 will no longer yield "Mohawk - Outside" from raw scraper fields.
